{"word":"H157 - אהב אהב - 'âhab 'âhêb - aw-hab'","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: אהב אהב"},{"paragraph":"Transliteration: 'âhab 'âhêb"},{"paragraph":"Phonetic: aw-hab'"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"வி.சொ - நேசமாயிரு. பிரியமாயிரு. அன்பாயிரு, சிநேகமாயிரு. விருப்பமாயிரு. பட்சமாயிரு. அன்புகூர், அன்புவை, சிநேகி, வாஞ்சி,ஆசை வை, மோகங்கொள்."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(1) to love"},{"paragraph":"(a) (in the Qal)"},{"paragraph":"(1) human love for another, includes love for family and sexual love"},{"paragraph":"(2) human appetite for objects such as food, drink, sleep, wisdom"},{"paragraph":"(3) human love for God or toward God"},{"paragraph":"(4) the act of being a friend"},{"paragraph":"(a) lover (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(b) friend (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(5) God's love toward mankind"},{"paragraph":"(a) towardindividual men"},{"paragraph":"(b) toward people Israel"},{"paragraph":"(c) to righteousness"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(b) (in the Niphal)"},{"paragraph":"(1) lovely (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(2) lovable (a participle)"},{"paragraph":"(c) (in the Piel)"},{"paragraph":"(1) friends"},{"paragraph":"(2) lovers (figuratively used of adulterers)"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"(2) to like"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Cognate: <a href=\"https://wordofgod.in/bibledictionary/ஸ்ட்ராங்க்ஸ்-எபிரேய-அகராதி/#/H157 - אהב אהב - 'âhab 'âhêb - aw-hab'/1578\">H157</a>, <a href=\"https://wordofgod.in/bibledictionary/ஸ்ட்ராங்க்ஸ்-எபிரேய-அகராதி/#/H158 - אהב - 'ahab - ah'-hab/1584\">H158</a>, <a href=\"https://wordofgod.in/bibledictionary/ஸ்ட்ராங்க்ஸ்-எபிரேய-அகராதி/#/H159 - אהב - 'ôhab - o'-hab/1593\">H159</a>, <a href=\"https://wordofgod.in/bibledictionary/ஸ்ட்ராங்க்ஸ்-எபிரேய-அகராதி/#/H160 - אהבה - 'ahăbâh - a-hab-aw/1603\">H160</a>"}]}